This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques applied to clinical data, specifically in the context of Alzheimer's disease. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as word embeddings and latent Dirichlet allocation, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with clinical data, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
